concept_explanation.the_immutability_cost:
Let's see why this matters. Compare these two methods that build a string from an array:

**Bad (using String +)**:

```java
public static String concatBad(String[] words) {
    String result = "";
    for (String word : words) {
        result += word + " ";  // creates a NEW string each time
    }
    return result.trim();
}
```

Each `result += word` does:
1. Read old `result` (n characters so far)
2. Allocate new string of size n + word.length
3. Copy all n old characters into new string
4. Copy word characters after
5. `result` now points to new string; old discarded

For 1000 words averaging 10 chars: ~5 million character copies. SLOW.

**Good (using StringBuilder)**:

```java
public static String concatGood(String[] words) {
    StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
    for (String word : words) {
        sb.append(word).append(" ");
    }
    return sb.toString().trim();
}
```

Each `sb.append(word)` just adds to an internal buffer. ~10,000 operations total. FAST.

**Real measurement**: For 10,000 string concatenations:
- String +: ~5 seconds
- StringBuilder: ~10 milliseconds

500x faster. This isn't a micro-optimization — it's the difference between code that ships and code that doesn't.

concept_explanation.string_join:
**`String.join(separator, items)`** — join an array of strings with a delimiter:

```java
String[] names = {"Aisha", "Raj", "Priya"};
String joined = String.join(", ", names);
System.out.println(joined);  // Aisha, Raj, Priya
```

Much cleaner than building manually:

```java
// Without String.join (clunky)
StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
for (int i = 0; i < names.length; i++) {
    if (i > 0) sb.append(", ");
    sb.append(names[i]);
}
String result = sb.toString();

// With String.join (clean)
String result = String.join(", ", names);
```

Common uses: CSV output, joining tags, building paths.

**Also accepts List** (covered in Collections module): `String.join(", ", myList)`

step_by_step_solution.details:
```java
StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();

// Header row
sb.append(String.format("%-20s %-15s %15s%n", "NAME", "DEPARTMENT", "SALARY"));
sb.append("-".repeat(52)).append("\n");
```

Notice:
- `%-20s` = left-aligned String in 20 char field
- `%-15s` = left-aligned in 15 chars
- `%15s` = right-aligned in 15 chars (no minus)
- `%n` = platform-appropriate newline
- `"-".repeat(52)` = 52 dashes for visual separator
- `.append(...).append(...)` chains nicely

```java
double totalSalary = 0;

for (String line : lines) {
    String[] fields = line.split(",");
    String firstName = fields[0];
    String lastName = fields[1];
    String department = fields[2];
    double salary = Double.parseDouble(fields[3]);

    String fullName = firstName + " " + lastName;
    String salaryFormatted = String.format("₹%,.0f", salary);

    sb.append(String.format("%-20s %-15s %15s%n", fullName, department, salaryFormatted));

    totalSalary += salary;
}
```

Notice:
- Parse line: `line.split(",")` → 4 fields
- Convert salary: `Double.parseDouble(fields[3])`
- Combine name: `firstName + " " + lastName` (a few concats, no StringBuilder needed)
- Format salary: `%,.0f` = number with commas, no decimals → "85,000"
- Append formatted row to sb
- Accumulate total

```java
String report = sb.toString();
System.out.println(report);
```

Final step: convert StringBuilder to String. We did all our work efficiently in the StringBuilder, then materialize the result.

worked_example.final_code:
public class CSVReportGenerator {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String csv = "Aisha,Khan,Engineering,85000\n"
                   + "Raj,Patel,Sales,72000\n"
                   + "Priya,Sharma,Engineering,92000\n"
                   + "Vikram,Mehta,Marketing,68000\n"
                   + "Anita,Gupta,Engineering,75000";

        String report = generateReport(csv);
        System.out.println(report);
    }

    public static String generateReport(String csv) {
        String[] lines = csv.split("\n");
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();

        // Header
        sb.append(String.format("%-20s %-15s %15s%n", "NAME", "DEPARTMENT", "SALARY"));
        sb.append("-".repeat(52)).append("\n");

        // Rows
        double totalSalary = 0;
        for (String line : lines) {
            String[] fields = line.split(",");
            String firstName = fields[0];
            String lastName = fields[1];
            String department = fields[2];
            double salary = Double.parseDouble(fields[3]);

            String fullName = firstName + " " + lastName;
            String salaryFormatted = String.format("₹%,.0f", salary);

            sb.append(String.format("%-20s %-15s %15s%n", fullName, department, salaryFormatted));

            totalSalary += salary;
        }

        // Footer
        sb.append("-".repeat(52)).append("\n");
        sb.append(String.format("%-36s %15s%n", "TOTAL", 
            String.format("₹%,.0f", totalSalary)));

        return sb.toString();
    }
}

